        "score": 0.05667649462505961,
        "text": "History of education in England\nThe 1891 Elementary Education Act provided for the state payment of school fees up to ten shillings per head, making primary education effectively free.",
        "score_breakdown": {
          "dense": 0.06769729891029175,
